    td.none.middle

p The BipolarType theory asserts that bipolar episodes are caused by a persistent skew in the cycle, either clockwise or counterclockwise.
table.none
  tr
    td.half.none
      table
        caption clockwise skew
        tr
          td
            b #{@realms.first.wise} #{Mood.j.foolishness}
            .left I feel #{Mood.j.foolish} when I cannot #{(@realms.first + Action.ep).wise}
          th
          td
            b #{@realms.second.wise} #{Mood.e.foolishness}
            .left I start #{(@realms.second + Action.ej).wise.ing} when I feel #{Mood.p.foolish} which doesn’t actually make me feel #{Mood.j.wise} enough, so I <em>keep doing it</em>, and then I cannot #{(@realms.second + Action.ep).wise} later so I don’t feel #{Mood.p.wise} either.
        tr
          th
          th=link_to Skew.first, type_path("#{@realms.join}#{Skew.first}")
          th
        tr
          td
            b #{@realms.fourth.wise}  #{Mood.i.foolishness}
            .left I start #{(@realms.fourth + Action.ip).wise.ing} when I feel #{Mood.j.foolish} which doesn’t actually make me feel #{Mood.p.wise} enough, so I <em>keep doing it</em>, and then I cannot #{(@realms.fourth + Action.ij).wise} later so I don’t feel #{Mood.j.wise} either.
          th
          td
            b #{@realms.third.wise} #{Mood.p.foolishness}
            .left I feel #{Mood.p.foolish} when I cannot #{(@realms.third + Action.ij).wise}

    td.half.none
      table
        caption counterclockwise skew
        tr
          td
            b #{@realms.second.wise} #{Mood.e.foolishness}
            .left I start #{(@realms.second + Action.ep).wise.ing} when I feel #{Mood.j.foolish} which doesn’t actually make me feel #{Mood.p.wise} enough, so I <em>keep doing it</em>, and then I cannot #{(@realms.second + Action.ej).wise} later so I don’t feel #{Mood.j.wise} either.
          th
          td
            b #{@realms.third.wise} #{Mood.p.foolishness}
            .left I feel #{Mood.p.foolish} when I cannot #{(@realms.third + Action.ej).wise}
        tr
          th
          th=link_to Skew.second, type_path("#{@realms.join}#{Skew.second}")
          th
        tr
          td
            b #{@realms.first.wise} #{Mood.j.foolishness}
            .left I feel #{Mood.j.foolish} when I cannot #{(@realms.first + Action.ip).wise}
          th
          td
            b #{@realms.fourth.wise} #{Mood.i.foolishness}
            .left I start #{(@realms.fourth + Action.ij).wise.ing} when I feel #{Mood.p.foolish} which doesn’t actually make me feel #{Mood.p.wise} enough, so I <em>keep doing it</em>, and then I cannot I  #{(@realms.fourth + Action.ip).wise} later so I don’t feel #{Mood.p.wise} either.
